<item>
  <title>Who’s leading the WNBA in 2026?</title>
  <dc:creator>Avery Regier</dc:creator>
  <link>https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/wnba/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>With March Madness, one of the most-watched sporting events, just rounding out the basketball season, fans are getting ready to watch the NBA draft and prepping for the new season. While lots of eyes are on men’s basketball, let’s not forget about the WNBA. Let’s be honest, we’ve all seen the Caitlin Clark and Angel Reese feud on our social media, but what about the rest of the teams? Where do they stand going into the next season?</p>
<p>This past season ended with the No.&nbsp;2 seed, the Las Vegas Aces, winning the playoffs, and the No.&nbsp;4 seed, the Phoenix Mercury, landing in the runner-up spot. The playoffs consisted of three separate rounds: a best-of-three first round, a best-of-five second round and a best-of-seven finals.</p>
<p>Wehoop, a R package designed to scrape WNBA data stats, from team box-scores, player box-scores and even play-by-plays, collected data from this past year to show the amount of rebounds and turnovers each team had throughout the season.</p>
